{{ 'kt-section-guide-teaser.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

{%- assign guide_teaser_heading_default = 'kt.section.guide_teaser.heading_default' | t -%}

{%- comment -%}
  R116 — hoist the `blogs[handle]` lookup once at the
  section root. Previously fired twice (header CTA + grid
  data resolution), each triggering a blog object hydration.
  Single assign reuses the resolved object across both
  branches.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign blog_obj = nil -%}
{%- if section.settings.blog != blank -%}
  {%- assign blog_obj = blogs[section.settings.blog] -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- assign has_live_articles = false -%}
{%- if blog_obj and blog_obj.articles_count > 0 -%}
  {%- assign has_live_articles = true -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- assign article_blocks = section.blocks | where: 'type', 'article' -%}

{%- comment -%}
  R-fresh-install-v2 — REVERTED the live-hide gate. CLAUDE.md
  "Empty States (Placeholders)" rule mandates `Never leave a
  blank or broken space when an image is missing` and the
  Shopify SVG placeholder fallback pattern. Hiding the
  whole section on live for fresh installs violated that
  spirit (the section's footprint went blank entirely).

  Correct approach mirrors the image-placeholder rule at
  the section level: ALWAYS render the section, fill empty
  state with Shopify SVG placeholders + onboarding-style
  text that's clearly merchant-directional, not generic
  "Article title goes here" filler. This is the pattern
  Skeleton (and Dawn before the rule split) uses and the
  one Theme Store reviewers expect on first install.
{%- endcomment -%}
<section class="kt-guide-teaser color-{{ section.settings.color_scheme | default: 'scheme-1' }} {% if section.settings.bg_color and section.settings.bg_color != 'auto' %}kt-section-bg--{{ section.settings.bg_color | replace: '_', '-' }}{% endif %}"
  style="{% if section.settings.bg_color == 'custom' and section.settings.bg_color_custom != blank %}--kt-section-bg-custom: {{ section.settings.bg_color_custom }};{% endif %}" data-section-id="{{ section.id }}" data-section-type="guide-teaser">
  <div class="page-width">
    <div class="kt-guide-teaser__header">
      <div>
        {%- if section.settings.label != blank -%}
          <p class="kt-guide-teaser__label">{{ section.settings.label }}</p>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- assign heading_tag = section.settings.heading_tag | default: 'h2' -%}
        <{{ heading_tag }} class="kt-guide-teaser__title">{{ section.settings.heading | default: guide_teaser_heading_default }}</{{ heading_tag }}>
      </div>
      {%- comment -%}
        R204 — "View All Journals" CTA was previously gated entirely
        on `blog_obj` resolving. With no blog selected (the
        fresh-install demo state), the button vanished even though
        the original Next.js source always shows it next to the
        heading. Two-tier resolution now: merchant's explicit URL
        setting wins, blog page is the natural fallback. If neither
        is set the button stays hidden so we don't render a dead
        link.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign view_all_url = section.settings.view_all_link -%}
      {%- if view_all_url == blank and blog_obj -%}
        {%- assign view_all_url = blog_obj.url -%}
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- if view_all_url != blank -%}
        <a href="{{ view_all_url }}" class="kt-guide-teaser__view-all">
          <span>{{ 'kt.section.guide_teaser.view_all' | t | default: 'View All Journals' }}</span>
          {%- render 'icon-arrow-up-right', width: 24, height: 24, stroke_width: 2 -%}
        </a>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    <div class="kt-guide-teaser__grid">
      {%- comment -%}
        Render-source priority (resolved up at the top of the file
        so the section root can gate on it):
        1. Live blog articles (if a blog handle was picked AND it has posts)
        2. Manual blocks (if any are configured)
        3. Placeholder cards — design_mode only (live storefront
           with no content branched out before opening the
           <section>; we never reach an empty band here).
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if has_live_articles -%}
          {%- for article in blog_obj.articles limit: section.settings.posts_count -%}
            <a href="{{ article.url }}" class="kt-guide-teaser__card">
              <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card-image-wrap">
                {%- if article.image -%}
                  {{ article.image | image_url: width: 800 | image_tag: class: 'kt-guide-teaser__card-image', loading: 'lazy', widths: '375, 550, 800', sizes: '(min-width: 750px) 33vw, 100vw', width: article.image.width, height: article.image.height, alt: article.image.alt | default: article.title }}
                {%- else -%}
                  {{ 'image' | placeholder_svg_tag: 'placeholder-svg kt-guide-teaser__card-image' }}
                {%- endif -%}
              </div>
              <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card-content">
                {%- if section.settings.show_category and article.tags.size > 0 -%}
                  {%- assign guide_teaser_primary_tag = blank -%}
                  {%- for tag in article.tags -%}
                    {%- assign tag_first_char = tag | slice: 0 -%}
                    {%- unless tag_first_char == '_' -%}
                      {%- assign guide_teaser_primary_tag = tag -%}
                      {%- break -%}
                    {%- endunless -%}
                  {%- endfor -%}
                  {%- if guide_teaser_primary_tag != blank -%}
                    <p class="kt-guide-teaser__card-category">{{ guide_teaser_primary_tag }}</p>
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endif -%}
                <h3 class="kt-guide-teaser__card-title">{{ article.title | escape }}</h3>
                {%- if section.settings.show_excerpt and article.excerpt_or_content != blank -%}
                  <p class="kt-guide-teaser__card-desc">{{ article.excerpt_or_content | strip_html | truncatewords: 20 }}</p>
                {%- endif -%}
                <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card-meta">
                  {%- if section.settings.show_author -%}
                    <span class="kt-guide-teaser__card-author">{{ article.author | escape }}</span>
                  {%- endif -%}
                  {%- if section.settings.show_date -%}
                    <time class="kt-guide-teaser__card-date" datetime="{{ article.published_at | date: '%Y-%m-%d' }}">
                      {{ article.published_at | date: format: 'abbreviated_date' }}
                    </time>
                  {%- endif -%}
                </div>
              </div>
            </a>
          {%- endfor -%}
      {%- elsif article_blocks.size > 0 -%}
        {%- comment -%} No live articles — use merchant-configured blocks {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- for block in article_blocks -%}
          {%- if block.type == 'article' -%}
            {%- comment -%}
              R165 GUIDE-TEASER-HTML-BALANCE-1: previously the
              wrapper opener (`<a>` vs `<div>`) and closer (`</a>`
              vs `</div>`) were each split across separate
              `{%- if -%}` blocks. While Liquid renders balanced
              markup at runtime, static HTML analyzers (Theme
              Check, axe pre-render, manual code review) flag the
              opener-without-matching-closer in source — and a
              reviewer reading source sees the unmatched tag pair
              as a Theme Store A11Y-6 ("valid HTML") concern.

              Capture the inner card markup once, then emit it
              inside a fully-balanced `<a>` block OR a fully-
              balanced `<div>` block. Each branch is now a single
              opener + closer pair that any static analyzer reads
              as valid. Behaviour identical: linked cards still
              render as `<a>`, unlinked still render as `<div>`.

              R162 EMPTY-HREF-1 rationale preserved: when the
              merchant hasn't linked the article yet, render the
              card as a non-clickable `<div>` for layout preview
              instead of `<a href="#">`.
            {%- endcomment -%}
            {%- capture guide_card_inner -%}
              <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card-image-wrap">
                {%- if block.settings.image != blank -%}
                  {{ block.settings.image | image_url: width: 800 | image_tag: class: 'kt-guide-teaser__card-image', loading: 'lazy', widths: '375, 550, 800', sizes: '(min-width: 750px) 33vw, 100vw', width: block.settings.image.width, height: block.settings.image.height, alt: block.settings.title | default: '' }}
                {%- else -%}
                  {{ 'image' | placeholder_svg_tag: 'placeholder-svg kt-guide-teaser__card-image' }}
                {%- endif -%}
              </div>
              <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card-content">
                {%- if block.settings.volume != blank -%}
                  <p class="kt-guide-teaser__card-category">{{ block.settings.volume }}</p>
                {%- endif -%}
                <h3 class="kt-guide-teaser__card-title">{{ block.settings.title | escape }}</h3>
                {%- if block.settings.description != blank -%}
                  <p class="kt-guide-teaser__card-desc">{{ block.settings.description | escape }}</p>
                {%- endif -%}
                {%- if block.settings.author != blank or block.settings.date != blank -%}
                  <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card-meta">
                    {%- if section.settings.show_author and block.settings.author != blank -%}
                      <span class="kt-guide-teaser__card-author">{{ block.settings.author | escape }}</span>
                    {%- endif -%}
                    {%- if section.settings.show_date and block.settings.date != blank -%}
                      <time class="kt-guide-teaser__card-date">{{ block.settings.date }}</time>
                    {%- endif -%}
                  </div>
                {%- endif -%}
              </div>
            {%- endcapture -%}
            {%- if block.settings.link != blank -%}
              <a href="{{ block.settings.link | escape }}" class="kt-guide-teaser__card" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                {{ guide_card_inner }}
              </a>
            {%- else -%}
              <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card kt-guide-teaser__card--unlinked" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                {{ guide_card_inner }}
              </div>
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
      {%- else -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          R-fresh-install-v2 — Onboarding empty state. Mirrors the
          CLAUDE.md image-placeholder rule pattern at the section
          level: Shopify `image` SVG placeholders + onboarding-
          directional text ("Add your first blog post" / "Connect a
          blog" via the dedicated kt.section.guide_teaser.empty_*
          locale keys), NOT generic "Article title goes here"
          filler that reads as unfinished demo content. Live
          storefront keeps the section visible — merchant first-
          install always has something to look at, never a blank
          stripe; Theme Store reviewer sees clear merchant guidance
          rather than fake article cards.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- for i in (1..3) -%}
          <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card kt-guide-teaser__card--placeholder">
            <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card-image-wrap">
              {{ 'image' | placeholder_svg_tag: 'placeholder-svg kt-guide-teaser__card-image' }}
            </div>
            <div class="kt-guide-teaser__card-content">
              <p class="kt-guide-teaser__card-category">{{ 'kt.section.guide_teaser.empty_label' | t }}</p>
              <h3 class="kt-guide-teaser__card-title">{{ 'kt.section.guide_teaser.empty_title' | t }}</h3>
              <p class="kt-guide-teaser__card-desc">{{ 'kt.section.guide_teaser.empty_desc' | t }}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        {%- endfor -%}
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script src="{{ 'kt-section-guide-teaser.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "t:sections.guide-teaser.name",
  "tag": "div",
  "class": "section",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "label",
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.label.label",
      "default": "Label"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.heading.label",
      "default": "Inspiration and guides"
    },
    {
      "type": "select",
      "id": "heading_tag",
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.heading_tag.label",
      "options": [
        {
          "value": "h1",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.heading_tag.options__1.label"
        },
        {
          "value": "h2",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.heading_tag.options__2.label"
        },
        {
          "value": "h3",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.heading_tag.options__3.label"
        },
        {
          "value": "h4",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.heading_tag.options__4.label"
        },
        {
          "value": "h5",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.heading_tag.options__5.label"
        },
        {
          "value": "h6",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.heading_tag.options__6.label"
        }
      ],
      "default": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.header__blog_source.content"
    },
    {
      "type": "blog",
      "id": "blog",
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.blog.label"
    },
    {
      "type": "url",
      "id": "view_all_link",
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.view_all_link.label"
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "posts_count",
      "min": 2,
      "max": 12,
      "step": 1,
      "default": 3,
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.posts_count.label"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.header__card_display.content"
    },
    {
      "type": "checkbox",
      "id": "show_category",
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.show_category.label",
      "default": true
    },
    {
      "type": "checkbox",
      "id": "show_excerpt",
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.show_excerpt.label",
      "default": true
    },
    {
      "type": "checkbox",
      "id": "show_author",
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.show_author.label",
      "default": true
    },
    {
      "type": "checkbox",
      "id": "show_date",
      "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.settings.show_date.label",
      "default": true
    },
    {
      "type": "select",
      "id": "bg_color",
      "label": "t:sections.shared.bg_color.label",
      "options": [
        {
          "value": "auto",
          "label": "t:sections.shared.bg_color.options__auto.label"
        },
        {
          "value": "white",
          "label": "t:sections.shared.bg_color.options__white.label"
        },
        {
          "value": "stone_50",
          "label": "t:sections.shared.bg_color.options__stone_50.label"
        },
        { "value": "stone_100", "label": "t:sections.shared.bg_color.options__stone_100.label" },
        { "value": "custom", "label": "t:sections.shared.bg_color.options__custom.label" }
      ],
      "default": "auto"
    },
        {
      "type": "color",
      "id": "bg_color_custom",
      "label": "t:sections.shared.bg_color_custom.label",
      "info": "t:sections.shared.bg_color_custom.info",
      "default": "#ffffff",
      "visible_if": "{{ section.settings.bg_color == 'custom' }}"},
{
      "type": "header",
      "content": "t:sections.shared.color_scheme.header"
    },
    {
      "type": "color_scheme",
      "id": "color_scheme",
      "label": "t:sections.shared.color_scheme.label",
      "default": "scheme-1"
    }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "article",
      "name": "t:sections.guide-teaser.blocks.article.name",
      "limit": 6,
      "settings": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "volume",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.blocks.article.settings.volume.label",
          "default": "Volume 1"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "title",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.blocks.article.settings.title.label",
          "default": "Article title goes here"
        },
        {
          "type": "textarea",
          "id": "description",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.blocks.article.settings.description.label",
          "default": "A short paragraph that introduces this section to your visitors and supports the heading above."
        },
        {
          "type": "image_picker",
          "id": "image",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.blocks.article.settings.image.label"
        },
        {
          "type": "url",
          "id": "link",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.blocks.article.settings.link.label"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "author",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.blocks.article.settings.author.label",
          "default": "Author name"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "date",
          "label": "t:sections.guide-teaser.blocks.article.settings.date.label",
          "default": "Date"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "disabled_on": {
    "groups": [
      "header",
      "footer"
    ]
  },
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "t:sections.guide-teaser.presets.name",
      "category": "Layout",
      "settings": {
        "posts_count": 3,
        "show_category": true,
        "show_excerpt": true,
        "show_author": true,
        "show_date": true
      },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "article",
          "settings": {
            "volume": "Volume",
            "title": "Article title",
            "description": "",
            "author": "",
            "date": ""
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "settings": {
            "volume": "Volume",
            "title": "Article title",
            "description": "",
            "author": "",
            "date": ""
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "settings": {
            "volume": "Volume",
            "title": "Article title",
            "description": "",
            "author": "",
            "date": ""
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
